<h2>Technical Stuff</h2>

<p>Since this is just a prototype (and a practice for BDD), I chose to use Ruby on Rails (RoR) and host this on Heroku. I plan to port this over to PHP and install it at UP-AME.org once people decide it's good enough.</p>

<p>One downside of getting it hosted in Heroku is the 5MB database limit. We can't upload pictures per member because of this and so we have to rely on image hosting sites.</p>

<p>Since this is just a prototype, I didn't bother hardening the site from malicious attacks. Aside from the login, there are no other security features in this site so please don't try to hack/break the site.</p>

